events.name: Chicago Bulls at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — For the Chicago Bulls, DeMar DeRozan's poise is as valuable as his points.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, LaVine help Bulls hang on to beat Knicks 119-115

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored 13 of his 29 points in the fourth quarter and the Toronto Raptors took advantage of Giannis Antetokounmpo sitting out with a sore right calf to beat Milwaukee 97-93 Thursday night, ending the Bucks’ winning streak at eight.
headlines.shortLinkText: Minus Giannis, Bucks lose to Toronto, ending win streak at 8

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — The game was long decided and the Memphis starters were relegated to cheerleaders on the bench when John Konchar got a steal and headed to the basket.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies throttle Thunder by NBA-record 73-point margin

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson and Cameron Payne both scored 19 points to lead the Phoenix Suns to their franchise-record 18th win in a row, beating the Detroit Pistons 114-103 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns push past Pistons, win franchise record 18th straight

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Bryn Forbes had 18 points off the bench and the San Antonio Spurs extended their winning streak to a season-high three games with a 114-83 victory over the shorthanded Portland Trail Blazers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Forbes leads Spurs in 114-83 win over shorthanded Blazers
